    <h3 itemprop="headline">Faking an honest woman: Why Russia, China and Big Tech all use faux females to get clicks</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      WASHINGTON (AP) — When disinformation researcher Wen-Ping Liu looked into China's efforts to influence Taiwan's recent election using fake social media accounts, something unusual stood out about the most successful profiles. They were female, or at least that's what they appeared to be.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2024/06/12/faking-an-honest-woman-why-russia-china-and-big-tech-all-use-faux-females-to-get-clicks-2/"  >(DAVID KLEPPER, Associated Press, KLAS, CBS News)</a>
